2002-01-05 [LOC Saudi Arabia] ( SA ) International ; military ; terrorism The [MISC Riyadh-based] [ORG Naif Arab Academy for Security Sciences] said in a statement that it was running a two-week workshop for 50 anti-terrorism experts . On 5 January 2002 pan-Arab anti-terror academy [ORG Naif Arab Academy for Security Sciences] reopened for the first time since the September 2001 terror attacks on the [LOC US] . [ORG Naif Arab Academy for Security Sciences] is based in [LOC Riyadh] . [ORG Naif Arab Academy for Security Sciences] is run by an [MISC Arab] Interior [ORG Ministers' Council] . In a statement [ORG Naif Arab Academy for Security Sciences] announced -- It will sponsor a 2-week workshop for 50 anti-terrorism experts . The workshop 's anti-terrorism experts are from 11 [MISC Arab] countries including [LOC Algeria] , [LOC Bahrain] , [LOC Egypt] , [LOC Jordan] , [LOC Lebanon] , [LOC Mauritania] , [LOC Morocco] , [LOC Saudi Arabia] , [LOC Sudan] , [LOC Syria] and [LOC Yemen] . The workshop 's anti-terrorism experts belong to anti-terror squads in [MISC Arab] security agencies and [ORG Anti-Organized Crime Units] . Some specialize in dealing with kidnapping and hostage-taking scenarios . The workshop will address several terrorism-related issues including political factors leading to terror , the role of religion in fighting terrorists and economic factors that support crime and terrorism . The workshop will study the use of the [MISC Internet] to promote terrorism and the [MISC Internet] 's role in facilitating money transactions and funding terrorist groups . In April 1998 [MISC Arab] countries signed an anti-terrorism agreement that binds the signatories to coordinate to fight terrorism . 2002-01-07 [LOC North Korea] ( [ORG KP] ) proliferation ; international A [ORG United Nation] nuclear team will make a week-long visit to [LOC North Korea] this weekend to inspect the [MISC Stalinist] state 's controversial nuclear site . Government sources said on January 7 , 2002 that a united nation nuclear team will make a week-long visit to [LOC North Korea] this weekend to inspect the [MISC Stalinist] state 's controversial nuclear site . The upcoming visit is viewed as part of the [ORG International Atomic Energy Agency] ( [ORG IAEA] ) drive to clarify [LOC North Korea] 's nuclear ambitions . A government source stated the visit by a group of [ORG IAEA] safety experts is scheduled to last for a week beginning January 12 , 2002 . The source stated that the inspection would focus on an isotope production laboratory in the [LOC Yongbyon] nuclear complex which is north of [LOC North Korea] 's capital [LOC Pyongyang] . The [ORG IAEA] tour of the isotope production laboratory will unlikely give a full picture of [LOC North Korea] 's suspected nuclear weapons ambitions . The tour was a surprise offer made by [LOC North Korea] in November 2001 . [ORG IAEA] accepted [LOC North Korea] 's proposal last month but cautioned that the proposal is not a breakthrough . [ORG IAEA] also stated the lab is not one of the frozen facilities it wants to look into . [ORG IAEA] is based in [LOC Vienna] and is the [ORG UN] 's nuclear supervisor . [LOC North Korea] has denied the [ORG IAEA] full access to its facilities . [LOC North Korea] froze its suspected nuclear weapons program at [LOC Yongbyon] in exchange for receiving two nuclear reactors producing less weapons-grade plutonium under a 1994 accord with the [LOC United States] . The 4.6-billion-dollar project was due to be completed by 2003 . Delays have pushed back the finish until at least 2008 . [LOC Pyongyang] insists it will allow full [ORG IAEA] inspections only when a significant portion of the project as defined in the 1994 accord is completed . 2002-01-11 [LOC South Korea] ( [LOC KR] ) International ; politics ; Telecom [MISC South Koreans] rallied on January 11 , 2002 in support of their right to eat dog meat . They threatened an [MISC Internet] war as part of a campaign to defend the traditi