] government has no knowledge of [ORG Al-Qaeda] having engaged in cyberattacks in the past but that leader [PER bin Laden] has suggested that if he chose to launch cyberattacks he could have the means available to him . In summary of the recent warning stating that such an attack could be executed in the very near future hensler-Hobbs stated that bin [PER Laden] 's location was irrelevant because bin [PER Laden] possesses the money and supporters necessary to have such an attack executed by others . A number of al-Qaeda militants including Millennium plot bomber [PER Ahmed Ressam] are known to have remained in [LOC Canada] . Many are located in [LOC Montreal] . [MISC Hensler-Hobbs] stated that the proliferation and availability of Hacker tools and the low skill level needed to conduct cyberattacks demonstrate the ease of launching an attack anywhere . [MISC Hensler-Hobbs] cited the example of the [MISC Montreal-based] Hacker known as mafiaboy who attacked [LOC U.S.] websites including [ORG Amazon.com] in 2000 . Many think that security must be improved at [MISC North American] critical infrastructures including energy and transportation providers and the financial services sector that are largely interconnected . Many businesses began preparing for cyber incidents before the year 2000 . A separate report issued recently by the [LOC U.S.] government-funded research group computer science and telecommunications Board stated that cyber security needs considerable improvement . For example , according to a [MISC Canadian] government estimate the love bug launched in May 2000 caused 6.7 billion [LOC U.S.] dollars in damage and disrupted [MISC Canadian] government systems . [ORG Bell Canada] spokesman [PER Andrew Cole] stated that [ORG Bell Canada] is prepared and remains prepared for various potential situations and scenarios . [PER Cole] stated -- [ORG Bell Canada] works very closely with the Government and the private sector to be aware of security concerns and to upda