. It made it more symbolic and indicated the willingness of those directly involved to eliminate the opium . The destruction forms part of the [ORG Central Committee] for [ORG Drug Abuse Control] 's project new destiny . It aims to prevent poppy cultivation by distributing seeds for substitution crops . Farmers have been asked to grow seven kinds of alternative crops across 21,969 acres ( 8,891 hectares ) of land instead of opium . Global narcotics authorities declared [LOC Myanmar] the world 's largest producer of opium in 2001 . They accounted for as much as 60 percent of global supply . [LOC Myanmar] beat [LOC Afghanistan] because the [ORG Taliban] militia 's enforced ban on opium poppies decreased [MISC Afghan] production by 90 percent . Critics said the [LOC Myanmar] regime overlooks much of the production and trafficking in drugs by ethnic insurgent groups . In particular the largest armed drug militia in the world the [ORG United Wa State Army] . [LOC Myanmar] 's Home Minister Colonel [PER Tin Hlaing] said the success of project new destiny is evidenced by the tons of poppy seeds that have been turned in rather than seized . [PER Hlaing] stated his confidence in the drug scourge that threatens the world will not find a place in [LOC Myanmar] if the local population is committed to this sort of cooperation . [ORG Lauk Kai] is one of the regime 's showpieces for its previous crop substitution programs . It has expanses of rubber trees , fruit orchards and paddy where poppies used to thrive . The poppies yielded the raw ingredient for heroin . [ORG Lauk Kai] is located in the infamous [MISC Golden Triangle] . Reformed drug lord and leader of the [LOC Kokang] phone [PER Kyar Shin] pledged commitment to the government program . The [LOC Kokang] comprise the majority of the population in [LOC Myanmar] . Phone [PER Kyar Shin] predicts that starting today there will be no destruction ceremony in the future because no more poppy will be grown . Phone [PER Kyar Shin] s