am which drives turbines to generate electricity . Plutonium and other radioactive byproducts of the process accumulate and decrease the effectiveness of the rods until they are spent after 3-4 years . Spent rods consisting of highly radioactive plutonium and residual uranium are cooled in pools of water for several years to diminish radioactivity and then the plutonium is then recovered in nitrate form and converted into oxide . The recovered plutonium can be mixed with uranium for reuse in the reactor or used in making nuclear weapons . Nuclear experts stated that to make weapons , a high proportion of plutonium 239 ( military grade plutonium , as opposed to the commercial plutonium used in power plants ) must be extracted . 2002-12-26 [LOC United Kingdom] ( GB ) proliferation ; international ; politics [MISC British] officials are deeply concerned by a warning from the [ORG International Atomic Energy Agency] ( [ORG IAEA] ) concerning [LOC North Korea] 's opening of the [LOC Yongbyon] facility and possible nuclear intentions . A [ORG UK Foreign Office] spokeswoman said Thursday that the [LOC UK] government is deeply concerned about the latest revelations in a warning by the [ORG International Atomic Energy Agency] ( [ORG IAEA] ) concerning [LOC North Korea] 's possible nuclear intentions . The comments came after the [ORG IAEA] accused the [MISC North Korean] government of nuclear brinkmanship and said the [MISC North Korean] government had begun work to reactivate the [LOC Yongbyon] reactor in breach of a 940000 agreement with the [LOC United States] Government . The [ORG UK] [ORG Foreign Ministry] spokeswoman said the [LOC UK] government is in regular contact with international partners about the implications of the latest developments and is committed to combat the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction wherever it may occur . The spokeswoman added that the [MISC North Korean] government must comply with international obligations and eliminate nuclear we