or slowdowns in [LOC Thailand] , [LOC Japan] , [LOC Malaysia] , the [LOC Philippines] , [LOC South Korea] and [LOC India] . [MISC Internet] service providers said a sudden surge in traffic jammed networks on the afternoon of 25 January 2003 . Antivirus vendor [ORG Symantec Corp.] estimated at least 22000 systems were affected worldwide . A technical support representative for [MISC Internet] [LOC Thailand] stated -- A virus or worm attacked a bug in microsoft software . While traffic among domestic [MISC Thai] servers was normal , exchanges with international servers began slowing down around 12:00 pm ( 0500 [MISC GMT] ) . The exchanges came to a halt within hours before recovering the evening of 25 January 2003 . [LOC U.S.] officials stated the attack sought out vulnerable computers on the [MISC Internet] using a known flaw in software from [ORG Microsoft Corp.] called [ORG SQL] server 2000 . The attacking software code scanned for victim computers randomly and aggressively and sent out thousands of probes each second which overwhelmed many [MISC Internet] data pipelines . Local [MISC Thai] subscribers stated that other [MISC Thai] [MISC Internet] service providers appeared to be unaffected . [ORG NHK] television in [LOC Japan] reported -- Some of the [LOC Japan] 's [MISC Internet] connections experienced heavy traffic . A public university computer had been hit by over 200000 transmissions in 1 hour . Security firms were investigating the incident . Traffic-directing computers at [ORG Korea Telecom] freetel and [ORG SK Telecom] failed to function in [LOC South Korea] and affected millions of [MISC Internet] users . Chief system engineer at [LOC KT] freetel [PER Kim Chang-Rae] stated excessive traffic caused 1 of [LOC KT] freetel 's main domain servers to fail which forced other servers to shut down in a chain reaction . Officials stated the system was restored after several hours but service remained slow . The failure affected weekend [MISC Internet] banking and 