[LOC Germany] . Foreign ministers , ambassadors and representatives of international organizations and observer nations met in [LOC Bonn] to discuss what form further talks should take . There are huge obstacles to achieving peace and cooperation among combatants in the former [LOC Yugoslavia] . [MISC German] Foreign Minister [PER Klaus Kinkel] said in opening remarks at the one-day meeting that there can be no peace in the former [LOC Yugoslavia] if some parties to the conflict remain heavily armed and others try to catch up . The [MISC Croation] delegation threatened to pull out of arms-reduction negotiations if certain demands were not met in the nearest future . Delegates from other countries called on [LOC Croatia] , [LOC Bosnia-Herzegovina] and [LOC Serbia] to set aside their grievances and learn to compromise . [MISC Croatian] Foreign Minister [PER Mate Granic] complained that a part of [MISC Croatian] territory is under occupation and time is running out . [PER Granic] said in reference to disputed lands on the [MISC Croatian-Serbian] border that the peaceful re-integration of [LOC Eastern Slavonia] is the key to the lasting stability in the region and that everyone faces the danger of another round of hostilities and the destabilization of the whole region and highly unpredictable consequences for [LOC Bosnia-Herzegovina] without it . Conference participants said Foreign Minister [PER Milan Milutinovic] from [LOC Serbia] scolded his [MISC Croatian] counterpart for grandstanding . Then [PER Milutinovic] made a threat to pull out of arms-control negotiations . [PER Milutinovic] noted the [MISC Serbian] Government has been suspended since 920000 from the [ORG Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe] and said that unless full membership were restored [LOC Yugoslavia] will be prevented from cooperating despite its readiness to do so . The [ORG OSCE] is to oversee the next round of [LOC Balkan] arms-reduction talks . [PER Michael Williams] is a senior fellow at the International Institute for [MISC Strategic Studies] in [LOC London] and formerly the [LOC United Nations'] senior spokesman for [LOC Croatia] and called the early threats from [LOC Croatia] and [LOC Serbia] a worrying development and an ominous development . [PER Williams] said it was really not clear that the parties are willing to engage in any arms control in a meaningful way . This corresponds to a fear expressed by some delegates to the 951218 [LOC Bonn] meeting that the yugolav parties do not want to negotiate away the ability to use violence or a threat of violence to seize territory . [MISC Greek] Foreign Minister karelos [PER Papoulias] observed of the [LOC Balkan] belligerents that during talk in the plenary session one realizes that this is still the way they are thinking . [PER Papoulias] said the [MISC Greek] government is not as optimistic as other [MISC European] partners and that just because there is a Conference doesn't mean there is friendship between the people of the former [LOC Yugoslavia] . The 951218 talks were organized to fulfill the combatants' pledge made in [LOC Dayton] , [LOC Ohio] , to begin talks to enhance mutual confidence and reduce the risk of conflict within 7 days of the Peace Accord 's formal signing . The agenda on 951218 was limited to set the formal process for coming weeks . The [MISC German] [ORG Foreign Ministry] said in a statement that this was so as to clear the way for speedy negotiation of the substantive questions . [LOC Croatia] , [LOC Bosnia-Herzegovina] and [LOC Serbia] are the nations that signed the [LOC Dayton] accord and are supposed to report how many tanks and armored vehicles , heavy artillery pieces , combat aircraft and attack helicopters they possess in the next phase . This data will be used to establish baselines from which weapons ceilings can be agreed on . [LOC Croatia] , [LOC Bosnia-Herzegovina] and [LOC Serbia] have promised to accept a set of automatic limits if agreement on such ceilings cannot be reached in 180 days . [PER Kinkel] said that on 951218 delegates had been unable to fix a date for the next round of talks but said the next talks would be 960104 or 960107 in [LOC Vienna] . [PER Kinkel] said minor problems not substantive discord kept delegates from choosing a firm date . 1999-06-30 [LOC India] ( IN ) ; [LOC Korea] , [ORG Democratic People 's Republic] of ( [ORG KP] ) International ; technology ; weapons ; government [MISC Indian] officials seize missile assembly line from the [MISC North Korean] vessel the kuwolsan on 30 June 1999 . The discovery heightens suspicions of [MISC North Korean] weapons proliferation . On 30 June 1999 [MISC Indian] customs agents in the northwestern port city of [LOC Kandla] boarded the [MISC North Korean] freighter kuwolsan . Following a melee with the crew of the kuwolsan , customs agents discovered an assembly line for ballistic missiles . [LOC U.S.] intelligence officials stated [MISC Libyan] government was the intended recipient of the cargo . The kuwolsan departed [LOC North Korea] 's [LOC Nampo] harbor on 10 April 1999 . Records show that on 20 April 1999 the kuwolsan made detours to 2 [MISC Thai] ports to pick up 14000 tons of sugar for resale along the way to the kuwolsan 's destination . The kuwolsan switched course in order to sell the sugar to an [MISC Indian] company after a deal to sell the sugar to [MISC Algerians] failed . An [MISC Indian] investigator stated that the crew of the kuwolsan should not have picked up extra cargo at several ports when carrying 200 tons of sensitive equipment and that such activity was crazy . [MISC Indian] customs officials were tipped off to possible contraband on the kuwolsan while the kuwolsan was en route to [LOC Kandla] . The kuwolsan was rumored to be carrying arms or ammunition possibly intended for [LOC Pakistan] . [MISC Indian] port officials were waiting when the kuwolsan arrived in [LOC Kandla] on 25 June 1999 . Irregularities in the kuwolsan 's papers were apparent within the first few hours of investigation . [MISC Indian] officials learned that the company in [LOC Malta] listed as the intended recipient of the cargo was fictitious . [MISC Indian] officials questioned why anyone in [LOC Malta] would choose to buy water refining equipment from [LOC North Korea] when [LOC Malta] is a short flight from [LOC Europe] . [MISC Indian] customs agents questioned the captain of the kuwolsan [PER Tae Min Hun] . [PER Tae] blocked every request and threatened international reprisals if [MISC Indian] officials did not allow [PER Tae] to leave [LOC Kandla] . On 30 June 1999 customs officials demanded to search the kuwolsan 's cargo boxes and [PER Tae] stated that the kuwolsan had received a telex from [MISC North Korean] officials . [PER Tae] received instructions from officials in [LOC Pyongyang] to allow no one to open the cargo boxes at all costs . The official [MISC Indian] after-action report stated [PER Tae] would not open any more boxes as per the telex . The report stated the crew members shouted at and abused the customs officers . According to witness accounts and video footage of the encounter , tae and the crew of the kuwolsan barricaded the doors of the kuwolsan with the crews' bodies . An [MISC Indian] official who was present on the kuwolsan and who spoke on the condition of anonymity stated the situation became physical and there were fisticuffs . The official stated the crew began closing the hatches to the cargo hold with the customs inspectors still inside . On 1 July 1999 armed troops and a group of government weapons experts aided customs officials and gained forcible entry onto the kuwolsan . A few crates among the kuwolsan 's cargo contained equipment that could be used in a water treatment plant . Inspectors found pumps , nozzles and a few valves . The cargo boxes were labeled as water refinement equipment . Documents from the investigation contain a partial list of the contents of most of the cargo crates which included -- Components for missile subassembly . [ORG Machine Tools] for setting up a fabrication facility . Instrumentation for evaluating the performance of a full missile system . Equipment for calibrating missile components . Rocket nose cones , stacks of metal pipe and heavy-duty presses used for milling high-grade steel . A Plate-bending machine capable of rolling thick metal sheets , toroidal air bottles used to guide warheads after separation from a missile , and Theodolites that measure missile trajectories . Several boxes of engineering drawings , blueprints , notebooks , textbooks and reports . Personal items presumably intended for [MISC North Korean] workers , including cookbooks in [MISC Korean] , [MISC Korean] spices , pickles and acupuncture sets . An [MISC Indian] government official familiar with the kuwolsan discovery stated that in the past officials had seen missiles or engine parts , but here was an entire assembly line for missiles offered for sale . The official stated that this was a complete technology transfer . A technical committee of [MISC Indian] missile experts stated that the equipment was unimpeachable and irrefutable evidence of a plan to transfer not just missiles but missile-making capability . The technical panel wrote in a report that the cargo points to only one end-use , namely the assembling of missiles and manufacture of the parts and subassemblies of surface to surface missiles . Investigators searched the blueprints that were kept inside numbered plastic jackets and wrapped in brown paper . Some of the packets were labeled in [MISC English] as [MISC Scud B] or [MISC Scud] [PER C. Nearly] all of the drawings showed rockets or sections of rockets with notes and mathematical formulas handwritten in [MISC Korean] . [MISC Native Korean] speakers assisted in translation but the documents contained technical code invented by [MISC North Korean] scientists to replace scientific terms in [MISC Russian] or [MISC Chinese] . The investigation ultimately yielded information about [LOC North Korea] 's weapons program which [MISC Indian] authorities shared with ally Governments . The [MISC Scud B] and [MISC Scud] C designs found on the kuwolsan were from older [MISC North Korean] missile programs which were derived from [MISC Soviet] missile designs of the 1950s . One [MISC Indian] government official who studied the blueprints stated the science was old and dated but still functional . Retired director of the [ORG State Department] 's Office on strategic , proliferation and military issues in the [ORG Bureau of Intelligence and Research] [PER Greg Thielmann] stated the [ORG CIA] utilized the blueprints to make full mock-ups of missiles complete with decals . The blueprints included information pertaining to the inner workings of [LOC North Korea] 's missile industry which has been the focus of contention between the [LOC United States] and [LOC North Korea] since the 1980s . The cargo on the kuwolsan did not include everything needed for missile production which raises the possibility that there may have been earlier and possible later shipments . Missile expert and senior analyst at the Center for [ORG Nonproliferation Studies] [PER Timothy V. McCarthy] examined some of the blueprints and other evidence and stated this was a slice in time of a technology transfer from [LOC North Korea] to [LOC Libya] . [PER McCarthy] stated the intelligence find helps [LOC U.S.] officials learn how [MISC North Korean] missile scientists learn . [PER McCarthy] stated the information gives [LOC U.S.] officials an idea of how capable [MISC North Korean] scientists are of progressing to more advanced missiles and gives [LOC U.S.] officials insight into the aspect of proliferation when one country 's officials attempt to transfer technology to another country 's officials . [PER McCarthy] stated no one can stop [MISC Libyan] scientists once the scientists are capable of making missiles . The kuwolsan and the crew were unaccounted for after [MISC Indian] officials released the kuwolsan in 2000 . Shipping experts at [PER Lloyd] 's maritime division in [LOC London] stated the kuwolsan 's name was changed in the summer of 2000 to [ORG Sun] grisan 9 . As of the week of 3 August 2003 the sun grisan 9 was still in service and was last reported headed to the [MISC Somalian] capital of [LOC Mogadishu] . The nature of the [ORG Sun] grisan 9 's cargo was unknown . As of 14 August 2003 the evidence from the kuwolsan is secured in a military warehouse in [LOC New Delhi] . As stated in court documents and interviews with officials in the [LOC United States] and [LOC India] the kuwolsan incident has reinforced a view of [LOC North Korea] as the world 's most dangerous source of weapons proliferation . In 1999 [MISC North Korean] leader [PER Kim Jong Il] expelled [ORG U.N.] inspectors , abandoned the [MISC Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty] and declared plans to build an atomic weapon . [LOC U.S.] intelligence officials stated that [MISC North Korean] officials are continuing global trade in technology for weapons of mass destruction including instructions for making advanced missiles . Successive [LOC U.S.] administrations have condemned [LOC North Korea] 's missile sales to such countries as [LOC Iran] and [LOC Syria] . On 31 August 1998 [MISC North Korean] officials launched a 3-stage missile which heightened fears of advanced [MISC North Korean] designs capable of reaching the [LOC U.S.] mainland . The first stage splashed down in the [LOC Sea] of [LOC Japan] , the second stage crossed the main island of [LOC Japan] and the third broke up and traveled 3450 miles downrange and fell into the [LOC Pacific Ocean] . The missile test fueled work on a [LOC U.S.] missile defense shield . [MISC North Korean] officials have defended the right to sell weapons and have stated that [MISC North Korean] officials are not bound by international treaties restricting such trade . [MISC North Korean] officials have sold missiles and parts to [LOC Yemen] which received 15 [MISC Scud] missiles after the missiles were briefly intercepted by [LOC U.S.] and [MISC Spanish] naval crews off the [MISC Yemeni] coast in December 1998 . [LOC Libya] appears to be the latest beneficiary of [MISC North Korean] weapons . Other nations including [LOC Iran] , [LOC Pakistan] and [LOC Syria] are known to have received similar help . The kuwolsan cargo attests to the existence of a gray zone composed of a combination of weak [LOC States] , open borders , lack of controls and a market of buyers and sellers of weapons of mass destruction . Small packages are sometimes delivered in the luggage of individual airline passengers such as a [MISC Taiwanese] businessman arrested at [LOC Zurich] 's airport in 2000 with [MISC North Korean] missile parts in a rucksack . Larger items are moved in freighters such as the kuwolsan while technical information and designs are accessible via the [MISC Internet] . [LOC Korea] specialist with the Center for [ORG Nonproliferation Studies] at the [ORG Monterey Institute of International Studies] in [LOC California] [PER Daniel pinkston] stated that intercepting weapons and equipment is difficult but not impossible but that human exchanges of plans , data , and intellectual property are difficult to intercept . 2002-04-06 [MISC Russian Federation] ( [MISC RU] ) International ; science ; energy ; weapons A high-security [MISC Russian] laboratory complex storing anthrax , plague and other deadly bacteria faces loosing electricity for lack of payment to the mosenergo electric utility . A large repository of anthrax , plague and other deadly bacteria stored in a high-security [MISC Russian] laboratory complex 100 miles south of [LOC Moscow] is facing the threat of loosing electricity . An official from the [LOC Moscow] region 's mosenergo electric utility arrived recently at the [MISC Russian] laboratory complex and threatened to turn off the electricity for lack of payment . The [MISC Russian] laboratory complex is a 90-building campus and served as the location for [LOC Russia] 's secret biological weapons program in the [MISC Soviet] era . An incorrect headline in the newspaper [ORG Izvestia] stated that deadly viruses from a [LOC Moscow] regional depository threaten [LOC Moscow] . There are no viruses at the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied Microbiology in obolensk . At the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology there is every kind of deadly bacteria that was studied for use in the secret biological weapons program of the [LOC Soviet Union] . A large virus repository is located in [LOC Siberia] . Both [MISC Russian] and [MISC Western] officials have stated that it is unlikely that any public health threat would result from a power cutoff at the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology . [MISC Russian] and [MISC Western] officials have stated that there is enough uncertainty that they could not be positive a loss of power at the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology would not cause a public health threat . General [PER Nikolai N. Urakov] stated by telephone that the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology has quite reliable systems of protection in case of emergency . General [PER Nikolai N. Urakov] is the longtime director of the the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology . The [ORG State] scientific center of applied microbiology has been working with [MISC Western] scientists to convert the complex into a biomedical manufacturing site . General [PER Nikolai N. Urakov] stated by telephone that the people at the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology are scared by this threat of a sudden shutdown of electricity because it is a kind of psychological pressure on the people at the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology . General [PER Nikolai N. Urakov] stated by telephone that in the event of a power shutdown at the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology scientists must destroy all bacteriological experiments under way . General [PER Nikolai N. Urakov] would like the [LOC United States] and [MISC Western] countries that have contributed about 6 million [LOC United States] dollars to the transformation of the former bioweapons complex to contribute another 500000 [LOC United States] dollars per year to pay the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology 's electric bills and arrears . An [MISC American] scientist who works closely with the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology stated that the [MISC Russian] government was responsible for paying for the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology 's electric bills . [MISC Western] aid for conversion of General [PER Nikolai N. Urakov] 's one time bioweapons laboratory peaked in 970000 because it was learned that [LOC Iran] had made offers to the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology to purchase its expertise . [MISC Russian] scientists and military leaders who now depend on [MISC Western] financing to destroy nuclear , chemical and biological weapons have been known to orchestrate a sense of crisis to increase financing . [MISC American] scientist [PER Randall Lee Beatty] is working on the conversion of the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied Microbiology in obolensk . [PER Beatty] stated that this threat to cut electricity to the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology is a crisis . [PER Randall Lee Beatty] is a Director of the [ORG International Science and Technology Center] . The [ORG International Science and Technology Center] finances approximately half of General [PER Nikolai N. Urakov] 's budget to support about 350 [MISC Russian] biowarfare scientists and technicians . [PER Randall Lee Beatty] stated that it is known that the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology has not paid its electricity bill for 14 months . [PER Randall Lee Beatty] stated that the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology is one of the important archives for dangerous pathogens in the world and it would be a shame if those archives were destroyed for not paying the electricity utility . Approximately 3000 strains of bacteria are stored at the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology and many of the bacteria are stored in cryogenic casks cooled with liquid nitrogen and isolated from the environment by layered enclosures and oversize air-handling systems that all depend on electricity to function . The greatest danger from a shutdown of electric power at the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology would be the defrosting of live germs that are currently preserved in a frozen state . A biological warfare expert at the [ORG Monterey Institute of International Studies] named [PER Raymond zilinskas] stated that the main threat from cutting power to the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied microbiology would be to the organisms themselves rather than that they might escape . [PER Raymond zilinskas] stated that in the worst case the bacteria would be defrosted from minus 70 degrees and it would be a real mess to clean up afterward because it would not be known for certain whether all the bacteria was dead . The confrontation between the mosenergo electric utility and the [ORG State Scientific Center] of applied Microbiology in obolensk is another example of how the basic capitalist imperative for enterprises to be self-sustaining can clash in a dangerous way with the old remnants of [MISC Soviet] weapons science . Due to an overdue power bill in 000000 the [MISC Russian] [ORG National Power Company] cut off electricity to a strategic base where nuclear missiles stood on high alert . The nuclear missile silos themselves did not lose power . Armed troops marched to the substations and turned the power back on . In 010100 and 010200 the national utility , [MISC United] energy systems cut power to a number of military installations around [LOC Russia] . The military installations that lost power included the [MISC Russian] space forces monitoring center on the [ORG Kamchatka Peninsula] . In most cases of military installations having their electricity cut off the electricity has been quickly restored . Often investigations show that the tug of war with the utility forces the military to spend budgeted funds for electrical power instead of diverting money for other uses . Some of the budgeted funds cut at times have included the building country residences for generals . 2004-07-24 [LOC Brazil] ( [ORG BR] ) International ; crime ; Government ; narcotics [LOC Brazil] to implement law allowing air force to target drug trafficking aircraft in [MISC Brazilian] airspace . [LOC US] concerned over liability in the event of misidentification of a civilian plane . [LOC Brazil] announced that the air force will begin shooting down aircraft used in trafficking illegal drugs in [MISC Brazilian] airspace . The plan requires 8 precautionary steps before the order to shoot down a plane may be issued . Prior to the policy taking effect late 20041000 a publicity campaign will notify ranchers and others of the need to file flight plans . The Law to permit such an action was originally approved in 1998 but 1995-2003 President [PER Fernando Henrique Cardoso] never put the policy into effect . The [LOC United States] dissuaded [PER Cardoso] from signing the decree out of concern that the accidental downing of civilian aircraft could expose the [LOC US] government and companies to lawsuits . 20010400 the [LOC United States] reduced previous support for operations targeting drug-running aircraft when a [MISC Peruvian] jet shot down a small plane misidentified as a drug carrier and killed an [MISC American] missionary and her child . Relatives of the victims sued the [LOC US] government and won a settlement due to the Government 's provision of intelligence and technical support to the operation . A [ORG US State Department] official stated -- [LOC US] law may forbid assistance to countries that implement shoot-down laws under certain conditions . The [LOC US] agrees with the [MISC Brazilian] assessment that the threat posed by drug traffickers is both very serious and increasing . The [LOC US] government has consulted the [MISC Brazilian] Government about the provisions of [LOC US] law . [MISC Brazilian] Defense Minister [PER Jose Viegas] stated that [LOC Brazil] has encountered difficulties in securing [LOC US] support for the plan but recent bilateral talks led to certainty that the decree would be accepted by the [LOC US] government without exposing [LOC Brazil] to commercial sanctions . [MISC Brazilian] officials have expressed hope that the policy will be endorsed by the [LOC US] before going into effect . The [LOC US] is scheduled to provide 10.2 million dollars in drug and law enforcement aid to [LOC Brazil] in 2004 . Former air force chief and current Director of the [ORG Air Institute] at estacio de sa University in [LOC Rio de Janeiro] General [PER Mauro Jose Miranda gandra] stated that the measure was a courageous step by the Government but the impact may be more political than practical because of self-imposed restrictions by the [MISC Brazilian] government . [MISC Brazilian] officials stated that the policy would be inapplicable against aircraft with children on board . [PER Viegas] stated that the limitation was necessary . [LOC Gandra] stated that the provision undermines the decree 's essential purpose by granting immunity to drug-smuggling aircraft carrying children and thus introducing the possibility of kidnapped children being used as human shields . [PER Viegas] stated in an interview in [LOC Brasilia] that the government will use the law to more powerfully dissuade drug traffickers who have previously entered [MISC Brazilian] airspace feeling unthreatened by the air force . The Government was prompted to act due to the deteriorating public security situation with increasingly powerful and violent drug gangs in [LOC Sao Paolo] and particularly [LOC Rio de Janeiro] . [LOC Rio de Janeiro] drug gangs have more firepower than the police and have successfully attacked police stations and forced businesses and schools to close . President [PER Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva] stated in a 2003 interview with foreign correspondents -- The policy is a matter of national sovereignty and security . Some pilots of drug-running aircraft felt so confidently immune from retribution as to make obscene gestures at pursuing [MISC Brazilian] air force pilots . The constitutionality of the law has been questioned under [LOC Brazil] 's prohibition of the death penalty as punishment for criminal acts . Some legal experts and other commentators stated that contrary to government claims , the Statute amounts to a de facto execution of drug traffickers . The daily newspaper [LOC O Estado de] [LOC Sao Paolo] stated in an editorial the week of 20040718-20040824 -- the extreme measure raises ethical and juridical problems exceeding any potential benefits . The penalty will be applied extrajudicially by administrative decision of the Commander of the [ORG Air Force] . This person will gain life and death power over crew members and passengers of irregular flights . In 2002 [LOC Brazil] inaugurated the 1.4 billion dollar SIVAM radar system allowing the government to monitor air activity throughout the expansive [LOC Amazon] region for the first time . The system uses [MISC American] technology . Illegal Flights initially declined 30 percent due to trafficker 's concerns about improved tracking capabilities but subsequently reaccelerated . [LOC Brazil] recorded 4128 unauthorized flights in 2003 . Some of these flights were innocent violations by ranchers in the [LOC Amazon] flying between plantations . [PER Viegas] stated that there was a significant increase in deliberate violations of [MISC Brazilian] airspace , apparently by drug smugglers realizing that the government was incapable of retaliation . 20010400 [LOC Rio de Janeiro] 's most notorious drug boss , [PER Fernandinho Beira-Mar] , was captured in [LOC Colombia] in a guns-for drugs pipeline involving left-wing guerrillas . [LOC Brazil] 's northern [LOC Amazon] corridor has become an increasingly busy and essential route in the global drug trade and is used for smuggling arms , gold and diamonds . Reportedly one of the most important drug- and gun-smuggling routes in supplying [LOC Europe] with cocaine runs from [LOC Colombia] across the northern tier of the [LOC Amazon] to [LOC Suriname] . [LOC Colombia] is the only country that currently has a policy of targeting drug trafficking aircraft . [LOC Colombia] is the source of much of the cocaine and heroin sold in the [LOC United States] . 2005-07-16 [LOC Venezuela] ( [ORG VE] ) International ; weapons ; leader ; military The [MISC Venezuelan] president 's weapons deals with [LOC Russia] , curbs on military cooperation with the [LOC United States] , and his plans to train as many as 2 million [MISC Venezuelan] civilians to repel a possible invasion by superpowers have the [LOC US] and his domestic critics worried . [MISC Venezuelan] president [PER Hugo Chavez] 's weapons deals with [LOC Russia] , curbs on military cooperation with the [LOC United States] , and plans to train as many as 2 million [MISC Venezuelan] civilians to repel a possible invasion by imperialist superpowers have the [LOC United States] and [PER Chavez] 's domestic critics worried about what the leftist former military officer is planning . [PER Chavez] insists that the moves are purely defensive and born of an overdue need to update obsolete military hardware and protect [LOC Venezuela] from nations that might want to take control of [LOC Venezuela] . [LOC Venezuela] is [LOC South America] 's largest petroleum-producing state . [PER Chavez] 's domestic opponents scoff at the idea that the [LOC US] would ever invade [LOC Venezuela] and charge that [PER Chavez] 's true intention is to arm a huge cadre of loyal reservists who would protect [PER Chavez] against any internal uprising and to pose as a militarized counterweight to [LOC US] influence in [LOC Latin America] . [MISC Cuban] leader [PER Fidel Castro] is [PER Chavez] 's his major ally and [PER Chavez] is growing closer to [PER Castro] . [PER Chavez] 's detractors in the [LOC US] government say that it is even more troubling that [PER Chavez] 's arms purchases and indoctrination of civilian militias could be part of a strategy to restructure [MISC Venezuelan] democracy in the image of [MISC Cuban-style] militarized socialism and foment leftist revolutions throughout [LOC South America] . [LOC US] military strategists say they are increasingly concerned that radical movements inspired by [PER Chavez] could foment such revolution . The political mainstream in [LOC Latin America] has shifted leftward since the late 1990s . This leftward shift is largely in reaction to the perceived failure of free-market economics . Leftists have been elected to lead [LOC Brazil] , [LOC Argentina] , [LOC Chile] , [LOC Uruguay] , [LOC Ecuador] and [LOC Venezuela] . [PER Chavez] 's supporters at home counter that the [LOC United States] has a century-long history of open as well as covert armed intervention in [LOC Latin America] 's domestic politics and say that it has no right to question [LOC Venezuela] 's defense preparations . [PER Carlos Roque Espinoza Leon] said that [MISC Venezuelans] never ask what the [ORG US Marines] are doing . [PER Espinoza Leon] is a pro-Chavez defense specialist who serves in [LOC Venezuela] 's [ORG National Assembly] . [PER Espinoza] said that [LOC Peru] has 500000 rifles and no one says anything . [PER Espinoza] said no one complains that [LOC Colombia] is the most militarized country in [LOC Latin America] . [PER Espinoza] said [LOC US] history is full of aggression in [LOC Latin America] . [PER Espinoza] said [MISC Venezuelans] have to do whatever is necessary to protect [LOC Venezuela] . [PER Chavez] has famously said that the [MISC Venezuelan] so-called [MISC Bolivarian] revolution is peaceful but not unarmed . [PER Chavez] was first elected in 980000 and has a popularity rating of 71 percent in an independent poll by polling firm [ORG Datanalisis] . [MISC Venezuelan] military analyst [PER Alberto Garrido] said [PER Chavez] is looking for allies in [LOC Russia] , [LOC China] , and [LOC Iran] in order to promote a multi-polar world which will counteract [LOC US] dominance and encourage grassroots Movements in [LOC Latin America] to throw off [LOC US] governmental influence . [PER Lorenzo Campos] is a farmer in [LOC Anzoategui] state in northern [LOC Venezuela] and is training as a reservist . [PER Campos] said [MISC Venezuelans] want the world to know that [MISC Venezuelans] are not preparing to attack anyone and that the mission is to protect [LOC Venezuela] . In May , [PER Chavez] 's government announced details in 050500 of an $18.6 million deal with a [MISC Russian] firm to purchase 100000 [MISC AK-103] assault rifles with 30 rounds of ammunition each and the technology transfer for [LOC Venezuela] to manufacture the rifles . The deal works out to $186.22 per rifle . This price is considerably less costly than the [LOC US] mail-order price of $825 to $850 for the same weapon . The Government of [LOC Venezuela] also intends to buy 10 [MISC Russian] helicopters , 10 [MISC Spanish] transport planes , and 6 [MISC Spanish] naval craft . [MISC Venezuelan] officials say the government is negotiating with [LOC Brazil] to buy around 24 air support and training planes . [PER Chavez] has insisted and even his staunchest retired military Critics here agree that the purchases are essential to update old weaponry such as the military 's decades-old [MISC Belgian] [ORG FAL] rifles . Retired General [PER Fernando OCHOA ANTICH] said that it is an exaggeration to say [PER Chavez] is engaged in an arms buildup . [PER Ochoa] was defense minister in 920000 when then-Lieutenant Colonel [PER Chavez] launched a failed coup . [PER Ochoa] stated that [LOC Venezuela] hasn't purchased arms in 25 years and said and [PER Chavez] is not aggressively buying weapons in a way that would threaten his neighbors . [PER Ochoa] said [LOC Venezuela] has never bought [MISC Russian] arms before and suggested [PER Chavez] is doing it to become independent from the [LOC US] . [PER Ochoa] asked why [PER Chavez] is buying a caliber of rifle which is popular among subversive forces in [LOC Latin America] and stated that the political support [PER Chavez] gives to radical leftist movements makes [PER Chavez] a continental menace . The [LOC US Pentagon] has openly questioned what [PER Chavez] will do with the old [ORG FAL] rifles and whether [PER Chavez] might share weapons or ammunition with guerrilla forces in [LOC Latin America] . The [LOC US] government has provided no evidence of [PER Chavez] arming or funding leftist insurgencies . Military analysts and specialists on the [MISC Colombian] [ORG FARC] guerrillas say the rebels have plenty of money for weapons from drug trafficking and would not be interested in old [MISC Belgian] rifles or in assistance from [PER Chavez] . A 030000 study published by the [ORG US Defense Intelligence Agency] reported that more than half of the weapons seized from [MISC Colombian] guerrillas from 980000 to 010000 that had markings of foreign militaries were of [MISC Venezuelan] origin . The implication was that corrupt or sympathetic members of the [MISC Venezuelan] military may be aiding guerrillas . Perhaps more distressing to [PER Chavez] 's domestic opponents is the ideological training that critics say [PER Chavez] has in mind for the military and for new civilian reservists . [PER Chavez] called earlier in 050000 for so-called Revolutionary units to start preparing the public to resist 